# 1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)

# 🔹 Attorney General of India (AGI)

The Attorney General is:

👉 **The highest law officer of India.**

Provides legal advice to the Government of India.

---

## 🔵 Constitutional Provision

### Article 76

Deals with Attorney General of India.

---

## 🔹 Appointment

Appointed by:

👉 President of India

---

## 🔹 Qualifications

Must be qualified to become a:

### Supreme Court Judge

Requirements:

* Citizen of India
* 5 years as High Court Judge OR
* 10 years as High Court Advocate OR
* Distinguished Jurist

---

## 🔴 Functions

Attorney General:

* Advises Union Government on legal matters
* Represents Government before Supreme Court
* Performs duties assigned by President

---

## 🔵 Rights of Attorney General

Can:

✅ Participate in Parliament proceedings

✅ Speak in Parliament

❌ Cannot vote

---

## 🔹 Removal

No fixed tenure.

Holds office during:

👉 Pleasure of the President

---

# 🔴 Advocate General of State

The Advocate General is:

👉 Highest law officer of a State.

Provides legal advice to State Government.

---

## 🔵 Constitutional Provision

### Article 165

Deals with Advocate General.

---

## 🔹 Appointment

Appointed by:

👉 Governor of State

---

## 🔹 Qualifications

Must be qualified to become a:

### High Court Judge

---

## 🔴 Functions

Advocate General:

* Advises State Government
* Represents State before High Court
* Performs duties assigned by Governor

---

## 🔵 Rights

Can:

✅ Participate in State Legislature proceedings

✅ Speak in Legislature

❌ Cannot vote

---

## 🔹 Removal

No fixed tenure.

Holds office during:

👉 Pleasure of Governor

---

# 🔵 Difference Between AGI & Advocate General

| Feature       | Attorney General       | Advocate General       |
| ------------- | ---------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Article       | 76                     | 165                    |
| Level         | Union                  | State                  |
| Appointed By  | President              | Governor               |
| Advises       | Central Govt           | State Govt             |
| Qualification | SC Judge Qualification | HC Judge Qualification |

---

# 🔹 Importance

These offices:

* Protect legal interests of Government
* Ensure constitutional governance
* Assist in legal decision-making

📌 They are not full-time government servants.

---

# 🔹 Important Facts

📌 Article 76 → Attorney General

📌 Article 165 → Advocate General

📌 AGI = Highest Law Officer of India

📌 Advocate General = Highest Law Officer of State

📌 Both can participate in legislature but cannot vote

